<h1 id="enablingmixedcontent">Enabling Mixed Content</h1>

<p><hr></p>

<p>Equella requires the use of mixed content, which Mozilla defines as &quot;loads of scripts, plugins, and stylesheets, from being loaded into a secure web page1.&quot;
This tutorial will show you how to enable this in all of the browsers that Blackboard supports:
Windows</p>

<ul>
<li>Firefox</li>
<li>Google Chrome</li>
<li>Internet Explorer</li>
</ul>

<p>Mac</p>

<ul>
<li>Firefox</li>
<li>Google Chrome</li>
<li>Internet Explorer</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="enablingmixedcontentinfirefox">Enabling Mixed Content in Firefox</h2>

<p>Firefox is blocking the &quot;insecure&quot; content. Click on the &quot;shield&quot; icon on the left side of the URL address bar, and then disable the blocking.</p>

<figure>
<img src="/Users/abuckingham99/Desktop/EnablingMixedContent/Enabling-Mixed-Content-in-Firefox.png" alt="Mixed" title="&lt;# Content #&gt;" />
<figcaption>Mixed</figcaption></figure>



<p><br></p>

<p>The page will refresh, and you'll be taken back to the home page. You'll see an exclamation mark inside a circle, letting you know that you have disabled the blocking.</p>

<figure>
<img src="/Users/abuckingham99/Desktop/EnablingMixedContent/Enabling-Mixed-Content-in-Firefox-1.png" alt="Firefox" title="&lt;# Title #&gt;" />
<figcaption>Firefox</figcaption></figure>



<p><br></p>

<h2 id="enablingmixedcontentingooglechrome">Enabling Mixed Content in Google Chrome</h2>

<p>If you click Tools --&gt; Equella Objects in Google Chrome, and nothing happens, check the location bar, to the left of the website. If you see a yellow triangle over the padlock icon, and a 'shield' icon on the right side, click on the shield.</p>

<p><img src="/Users/abuckingham99/Desktop/EnablingMixedContent/Enabling-Mixed-Content-in-Google-Chrome.png" alt="Google Chrome" title="&lt;# Title #&gt;" /></p>

<p><br></p>

<p>This is a close up of the padlock icon on the left side of the URL address bar. If you see this yellow triangle, click on the shield on the right side of the address bar.</p>

<p><img src="/Users/abuckingham99/Desktop/EnablingMixedContent/Enabling-Mixed-Content-in-Google-Chrome-1.png" alt="Close-up of the padlock icon" title="&lt;# Title #&gt;" /></p>
